candidate_text:
 Confirmation Hearings: They have advisory consent powers giving opinions, reviewing nominations, the chief executive's (President) appointments of Supreme Court justices other high-ranking government officials like Cabinet members Ambassadors &amp; Federal Judges requiring Senate confirmation.

Some additional key responsibilities are:
Listening to constituent concerns;
Communicating effectively with fellow elected officials;
Serving in various committee assignments;
Holding hearings and investigations;

Overall the duties require effective communication skills, negotiation collaboration coalition-building problem-solving leadership.assistant

The main responsibilities of a United States Senator are multifaceted and critical to the country's governance.
